explanation: This solution uses two stacks to simulate a queue. The `push` operation is O(1) as it simply pushes the element onto the `stackNewestOnTop`. The `pop` and `peek` operations are O(1) amortized as they may need to transfer elements from `stackNewestOnTop` to `stackOldestOnTop` in O(n) time, but this is done only when `stackOldestOnTop` is empty. The `empty` operation is O(1) as it simply checks if both stacks are empty. The space complexity is O(n) as in the worst case, all elements are stored in `stackOldestOnTop`.

